wiki.text:
'Ubi' may refer to:

* Ubi Dwyer, founder of the Windsor Free Festival
* UBI World TV, Australian digital satellite pay television service.
* Ubi, Singapore, also known as Ubi Estate, a residential and industrial area
  in Singapore
* Ubisoft, a video game publisher and developer
* Ube or ubi or purple yam (among other names), a vegetable of the yam family
* Ubi language, an Afro-Asiatic language spoken in Central Chad.

'UBI' may also refer to:

* Union Brazilian pro Interlingua, the national Interlingua organization in
  Brazil
* University of Beira Interior, a Portuguese public university
* Union Bank of India, one of India's largest state-run banks, inaugurated by
  Mahatma Gandhi
* United Bank of India, major commercial bank in India, nationalised in 1969
* Unsorted Block Images, a volume management system for raw flash devices.
* United Bicycle Institute, a bicycle mechanics and frame building school in
  Oregon, USA
*  Universal Basic Income, an unconditional, non-means tested social dividend.
* Usage-based insurance, a method of variable payment for auto insurance based
  on usage data
